 Fixing SQLAlchemy/Pydantic Model Conflict in FastAPI

Problem:
You get this error when querying the database:
sqlalchemy.exc.ArgumentError: Column expression, FROM clause, or other columns clause element expected, got <class 'app.schemas.document_schema.Document'>
Cause:
You’re importing both the SQLAlchemy and Pydantic Document models with the same name:
from app.models.models import Document          # ✅ SQLAlchemy
from app.schemas.document_schema import Document        # ❌ Pydantic (overwrites the first one)

So db.query(Document) ends up using the wrong one (Pydantic), causing the error.

Fix:
Rename the imports to avoid conflict:
from app.models.models import Document as DocumentModel
from app.schemas.document_schema import Document as DocumentSchema
Use:
	•	DocumentModel for all database queries
	•	DocumentSchema for response_model= or output serialization

Result:
The error disappears, and database queries work as expected.



